<div class="ds-eyebrow">Component library · mobile</div>
<h1 class="ds-title">Mobile components</h1>
<p class="ds-lede">The mobile counterpart of every desktop component. Below the 600px breakpoint each golden page swaps its desktop chrome for a purpose-built mobile layer (the <code>.m-*</code> system in <code>responsive.css</code>); these specimens render that layer inside a 390px phone frame. One entry per desktop component, so the two catalogs line up one-to-one.</p>
<div class="ds-example-grid">
{% for c in mobileManifest.components %}
  <a class="ds-component-card" href="/mobile/{{ c.id }}/">
    <span class="cat">{{ c.category }}</span>
    <h3>{{ c.name }}</h3>
    <p>{{ c.purpose }}</p>
  </a>
{% endfor %}
</div>
